  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Mask wearing during the Covid-19 pandemic has been proven substantially effective in&#xD;
      containing the spread of infection, with cloth masks being the most universally used.&#xD;
      However, cloth masks may be uncomfortable and have physiological repercussion during&#xD;
      exercise. This study aims to investigate the impact of cloth masks during exercise.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
